64 17 saepibus . . . interiectis: cf. note on 60 25.

64 18 ante: i.e. in ch. 17. —impedireturz connected with resisterent by -que in 1. 17.

64 19 neque: here begins the main clause, the verb of which is poterant.

64 20 provideri: complem. infin. with poterat supplied from poterant. The subject of this poterat is the indir. quest. quid . . . opus esset.—ab uno (emphatic), by only one man.

64 21 fortunae: emphatic, set off against rerum. The circumstances were diversified; the fortune that attended them consequently had various results.

64 22 eventus (nom. plur.): subject of sequebantur.
